The Enugu zonal office of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), has arrested four suspected fraudsters. Wilson Uwujaren, Head, Media and Publicity, said they were arrested at shop 22, Image Digital Studio, Jo-Josh Mall, Ikenegbu, Owerri, Imo State, following intelligence that the suspects were operating an illegal business centre which specialised in the procurement and sale of forged documents. They allegedly edit and sell documents of multinational companies, identity cards of Nigerian and foreign banks and photographs of foreigners to unidentified Internet fraudsters. Uwujaren said several mobile phones, four central processing units(CPU), several fake identity cards bearing the names ofÂ  companies located both home and abroad, a Toshiba laptop computer and two colour printers were recovered from the suspects. He said the suspects have made useful statements and would be charged to court as soon as investigation is concluded.